\section{Dataset}

\subsection{CASIA v2.0}

All experiments use the \textbf{CASIA v2.0} dataset~\cite{dong2013casia}, a widely-used benchmark for image forgery detection and localization.

\begin{table}[H]
\centering
\caption{CASIA v2.0 Dataset Summary}
\label{tab:dataset}
\begin{tabular}{l r}
\toprule
\textbf{Property} & \textbf{Value} \\
\midrule
Total images & 12,614 \\
Authentic images & 7,491 (59.4\%) \\
Tampered images & 5,123 (40.6\%) \\
\quad Copy-move forgeries & 3,295 (26.1\%) \\
\quad Splicing forgeries & 1,828 (14.5\%) \\
Ground truth & Binary masks \\
Image formats & JPEG, BMP, TIFF \\
Resolution range & Variable (resized to 384$\times$384) \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

\subsection{Data Splitting}

The dataset is split using a two-step stratified process with seed 42:

\begin{enumerate}[nosep]
    \item 70/30 split of the full dataset (stratified by authentic/tampered label).
    \item 50/50 split of the 30\% holdout into validation and test sets.
\end{enumerate}

\begin{table}[H]
\centering
\caption{Data Split Configuration}
\label{tab:split}
\begin{tabular}{l r r l}
\toprule
\textbf{Split} & \textbf{Count} & \textbf{Ratio} & \textbf{Purpose} \\
\midrule
Training & 8,829 & 70\% & Model optimization \\
Validation & 1,892 & 15\% & Early stopping, LR scheduling \\
Test & 1,893 & 15\% & Final reported metrics \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

\subsection{Preprocessing}

\begin{itemize}[nosep]
    \item All images resized to $384 \times 384$ pixels using bilinear interpolation.
    \item Ground truth masks resized with nearest-neighbor interpolation, then binarized at threshold 0.5.
    \item Per-channel normalization statistics computed from 500 randomly sampled training images.
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Data Leakage Discovery}

An important finding during the project was that the Kaggle variant of the CASIA dataset mixed ground truth mask images into the input data folder. A CNN trivially distinguished mask images (simple binary patterns) from real photographs, producing 100\% ``test accuracy.'' This result was discarded, and the discovery motivated strict pipeline audits in all subsequent experiments.

